details:
Case 176 is an imported case involving a 37 year-old female British national who works in Singapore, and had been in Japan from 24 February to 4 March, and the UK from 4 March to 8 March. She is warded in an isolation room at National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID).

She reported onset of symptoms on 7 March while in the UK and had sought treatment at Gleneagles Hospital on 10 March. She was conveyed by ambulance to National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID) on the same day. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 11 March morning.

She stays in the Dover Road area.
